      • getGenericType

        public java.lang.reflect.Type getGenericType()
        Returns a Type object that represents the declared type for the field represented by this RawField object.

        If the Type is a parameterized type, the Type object returned must accurately reflect the actual type parameters used in the source code.

        If the type of the underlying field is a type variable or a parameterized type, it is created. Otherwise, it is resolved.

        The implementation of this method must follow the contract given for Field.getGenericType()

        Returns:
        the generic type of the field
        See Also:
        Field.getGenericType()

      • getValue

        public java.lang.Object getValue(java.lang.Object owningInstance)
                          throws java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Returns the value of the field represented by this RawField, on the specified owningInstance. The value is automatically wrapped in an object if it has a primitive type.

        The implementation of this method must follow the contract given for Field.get(Object)

        Parameters:
        owningInstance - object from which the represented field's value is to be extracted
        Returns:
        the value of the represented field in owningInstance. primitive values are wrapped in an appropriate object before being returned
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - if this RawField object is enforcing Java language access control and the underlying field is inaccessible.
        See Also:
        Field.get(Object)

      • setValue

        public void setValue(java.lang.Object owningInstance,
                     java.lang.Object value)
              throws java.lang.IllegalAccessException
        Sets the field represented by this RawField object on the specified object argument to the specified new value. The new value is automatically unwrapped if the underlying field has a primitive type.

        The implementation of this method must follow the contract given for Field.set(Object, Object).

        Parameters:
        owningInstance - the object whose field should be modified
        value - the new value for the field of owningInstance being modified
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalAccessException - if this RawField object is enforcing Java language access control and the underlying field is inaccessible.
        See Also:
        Field.set(Object, Object)
